theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (h : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure A = closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  ·
    -- First, rewrite `closure A` using the equality obtained from `P1`.
    have hEq : closure A = closure (interior A) :=
      Topology.closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P1 (A := A) h
    -- Show that `closure (interior A)` is contained in `closure (interior (closure A))`.
    have hSub : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
      have hInner : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
        interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
      exact closure_mono hInner
    simpa [hEq] using hSub
  ·
    -- The interior of a set is always contained in the set itself.
    exact closure_mono
      (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)
